<body> 
  <div id="main"> 
    <div id="top-banner1"> 
    </div> 
    <div id="top-banner2"> 
        Hot Framework
    </div> 
    <div id="middle"> 
        <p> 
        Congratulations! You just come to create your first web application with the hot framework. To develop your app, just create scripts or pages in the programming language of your choice.
        </p> 
        <p> 
         Following programming languages are actually supported:
            <ul> 
                <li>Groovy</li> 
                <li>Python</li> 
                <li>Javascript</li> 
            </ul> 
        </p> 
        <p> 
            Your project directory has the following structure
        </p> 
        <div class="code"> 
            <ul style="list-style-type: none;"> 
                <li>|-work</li> 
                <li>|-<b>www</b></li> 
                <li>\</li> 
                <li> 
                    <ul style="list-style-type: none;"> 
                        <li>|-&lt;your scripts&gt;</li> 
                    </ul> 
                </li> 
                <li>|-config.js</li> 
            </ul> 
        </div> 
        <p> 
            Scripts and pages must be created in the <b>www</b> folder.
        </p> 
        <h2>Writing scripts</h2> 
        <p> 
            In case you wish write scripts, let's just create <b>.groovy</b>, <b>.py</b> or <b>.js</b> files corresponding respectively to Groovy, Python or Javascript language in the <b>www</b> folder
        </p> 
        <p> 
            For exemple, let's consider the following python script fibonacci.py
        </p> 
        <div class="code"> 
            print &ldquo;&lt;html&gt;&ldquo;<br> 
            print &ldquo;&lt;body&gt;&ldquo;<br> 
            print &ldquo;&lt;ul&gt;&ldquo;<br> 
            <br> 
            fi = 0<br> 
            fii =1<br> 
            for i in range (10):<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;fiii = fi + fii<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;print &ldquo;&lt;li&gt;&ldquo;+fiii+&ldquo;&lt;/li&gt;&ldquo;<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;fi = fii<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;fii = fiii<br> 
            <br> 
            print &ldquo;&lt;/ul&gt;&ldquo;<br> 
            print &ldquo;&lt;/body&gt;&ldquo;<br> 
            print &ldquo;&lt;/html&gt;&ldquo;<br> 
        </div> 
        <h2>Writing Hot pages</h2> 
        <p> 
            Hot framework lets you create dynamic web pages in the same way you do in PHP. Simply embed Javascript, Python or Groovy fragments in your html page. 
        </p> 
        <p> 
            Javascript will be embedded in <b>.hjs</b> files, Groovy in <b>.hotg</b> files and Python in <b>.hotp</b> files.
        </p> 
        <p> 
            Let's consider the following hot page fibonacci.hjs embedding Javascript code
        </p> 
        <div class="code"> 
            &lt;html&gt;<br> 
            &lt;body&gt;<br> 
            &lt;ul&gt;<br> 
            &lt;?hot&nbsp;<br> 
            <br> 
            var fi = 0&#59;<br> 
            var fii =1&#59;<br> 
            for (i = 0&#59; i &lt; 10&#59; ++i) {<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;var fiii = fi + fii&#59;<br> 
            ?&gt;<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li&gt;&lt;?hot&nbsp; hprint(fiii)&#59; ?&gt; &lt;/li&gt;<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;?hot&nbsp;<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;fi = fii&#59;<br> 
            &nbsp;&nbsp;fii = fiii&#59;<br> 
            } ?&gt;
            <br> 
            &lt;/ul&gt<br> 
            &lt;/body&gt;<br> 
            &lt;/html&gt;<br> 
        </div> 
        <p> 
            Thank you for choosing Hot framework! Have Fun!
        </p> 
    </div> 
    <div id="bottom"> 
    </div> 
</div> 
  
</body> 
 
 
